# UI Handoff Quality

A UI spec is implementation-ready only if it includes:
- Scope (in/out)
- Screen states (loading, empty, error, success)
- Navigation rules
- Validation rules
- Responsive behavior
- Accessibility notes
- Acceptance checklist with pass/fail wording

If any item is missing, request spec completion before implementation.
